title: Detroit mural credited to Banksy sells for $137,500
text: > Entertainment Detroit mural credited to Banksy sells for $137,500 FILE - This May 11, 2010 file photo shows the founders of the art gallery 555 Arts, Carl W. Goines, left, and Monte Martinez, wrapping artwork by popular graffiti artist Banksy at the abandoned Packard car plant in Detroit. An auction is planned for an artwork that gallery officials say the elusive British graffiti artist Banksy created at a former Detroit auto plant. It's listed among works being sold during a "Street Art" auction by Julien's Auctions in Beverly Hills, California. (AP Photo/Jerry S. Mendoza, File)
